---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const faqData = [
  {
    question: "Is Costco hot dog kosher?",
    answer: "No. Costco hot dogs are not certified kosher by any recognized kosher authority."
  },
  {
    question: "Does Costco sell kosher hot dogs?",
    answer: "Some Costco locations stock kosher-certified products in the refrigerated section, but the food court hot dog is not kosher."
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Is Costco Hot Dog Kosher?"
  description="No — Costco hot dogs are not kosher certified. Learn about kosher status and alternatives."
  type="faq"
  faqData={faqData}
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-8 text-center mb-10">
      <p class="text-sm text-yellow-700 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide">Answer</p>
      <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-yellow-800 mt-2">No</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-700 mt-2">Not kosher certified</p>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Is Costco Hot Dog Kosher?</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Understanding kosher certification and what it means for observant Jewish shoppers.</p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Kosher Requirements</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">For meat to be kosher, it must come from a kosher animal (beef qualifies), be slaughtered according to shechita by a trained shochet, and be processed under rabbinical supervision. Costco hot dogs do not meet these certification requirements.</p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Alternatives</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Some Costco warehouses carry kosher-certified products in the grocery section. Look for brands with OU, OK, or Star-K certification symbols.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
